          "date_description"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "en": [
          "<P>Waywell dates the Mattei Athena itself to ca. 130-90 BC, on the assumption that such scale copies were not made in Athens before the period of Roman control in Greece (beginning in 146 BC) and that it should predate Sulla's sack in 87/86 BC, when the Piraeus Athena, presumably its model, was apparently removed from its original location and was lost. He dates the Piraeus Athena, archetype of the Mattei, to ca. 475 BC on the basis of style. See further notes under subject.</P>"
        ]
      }
